  "text": "American younger adults (aged 20-39 years) live with obesity but a smaller proportion have hyperlipidemia compared to White younger adults in the National Health and Nutrition Examination Surveys [CITATION_1] . We also found that persons of non-White race/ethnicity make up a majority of young adults who engage in DEBs and may be important populations for screening and future research.",
